Privacy Policy for Voice Gmail
Overview
Voice Gmail is a voice-activated email assistant application that helps users send emails and check their inbox using voice commands.

Information We Collect
User Data: Voice Gmail may collect and store user data, including email addresses, message content, and contact information, to provide its core functionality.
How We Use Information
Application Functionality: User data is used solely to enable the core functionality of Voice Gmail, such as sending emails and checking the inbox based on voice commands.
Data Security
Encryption: Voice Gmail employs encryption to secure user data during transmission and storage.
Third-Party Access
Third-Party Services: Voice Gmail may use third-party services for email delivery and authentication. These services adhere to their own privacy policies.
User Controls
Data Access: Users can control access to their data by managing permissions in the Voice Gmail application settings.
Changes to this Privacy Policy
Updates: This privacy policy may be updated to reflect changes in the application or legal requirements. Users will be notified of any significant changes.
Contact Us
Questions: If you have any questions or concerns about this privacy policy, please contact us at jainsarthak.7502@gmail.com.
